&lt;p&gt;After glorifying plotly express, it is natural to find some drawbacks. Has plotly express some limitations? Particularly, how much data can we put into it? According to them, there is no hard limit for data set size but it is preferable to use 1000 points for some chart types and make some input parameter adjustments, while other chart types easily handle more points. I'm still trying to figure out the mechanics of plotly express and dig deeper, however, it won't be a bad idea to check more, about plotly express &lt;a href="https://medium.com/@plotlygraphs/introducing-plotly-express-808df010143d"&gt;here&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;
